# SetupWizard

## Summary

First-run setup wizard that the isolated planner shows over the canvas until the plan has content. It is a thin wrapper composing the shared catalog `<Stepper>` component (`@cardstack/catalog/aef6db-stepper/stepper`), which supplies the modal scrim, vertical step rail, heading, and Back/Next navigation; this file owns only the four domain steps — event details (name, date, venue), hosts (the couple), guests, and finally starting from a layout template (previewed with LayoutPreview) or a blank canvas — plus the gold corner ornament, expressed as `StepperStep` descriptors with per-step `isComplete` checks. It talks to the host planner only through args: every mutation happens via the callbacks you pass in, and the planner's `hosts` / `guests` linksToMany field components are passed as `@hostsField` / `@guestsField` so newly added people render as fitted cards inside the wizard. Every step is mandatory — Next stays disabled until the step is complete (all three event fields, at least one host, at least one guest) and there is no Skip; the ✕ close (and the final "Start blank" finish action, both wired to `@onSkip`) is the one escape hatch, and dismissal isn't persisted, so the wizard reopens the next time an incomplete planner is opened.

## Import

```js
import SetupWizard from '../components/setup-wizard';
```

## Template Usage

As invoked from the isolated planner view:

```gjs
<SetupWizard
  @hostsField={{@fields.hosts}}
  @guestsField={{@fields.guests}}
  @eventTitle={{@model.eventTitle}}
  @venue={{@model.venue}}
  @eventDate={{this.eventDateInput}}
  @guestCount={{this.totalGuests}}
  @hostCount={{this.hostsCount}}
  @templates={{this.templates}}
  @templatesLoading={{this.templatesLoading}}
  @onEventTitle={{this.setEventTitle}}
  @onVenue={{this.setVenue}}
  @onEventDate={{this.setEventDate}}
  @onAddHosts={{this.addHosts}}
  @onAddGuests={{this.addGuests}}
  @onLoadTemplates={{this.loadTemplates}}
  @onApplyTemplate={{this.applyTemplateFromWizard}}
  @onSkip={{this.skipWizard}}
/>
```
